# AI Semantic Caching

## Configuration options

The AI Semantic Caching policy requires configuration of an embedding model resource and a vector store resource. All parameters support Gravitee Expression Language (EL) for dynamic values.

### Policy-level configuration

| Name<br>`json name` | Type<br>`constraint` | Mandatory | Default | Description |
|:--------------------|:---------------------|:---------:|:--------|:------------|
| Embedding model resource<br>`modelName` | string | ✅ | | The AI text embedding model resource used to generate vector representations of request content. |
| Vector store resource<br>`vectorStoreName` | string | ✅ | | The vector store resource used to store and retrieve cached vectors. |
| Prompt expression<br>`promptExpression` | string | | `{#request.content}` | Expression to extract content from the request for embedding generation. Supports JSONPath for structured data extraction. |
| Cache condition<br>`cacheCondition` | string | | `{#response.status >= 200 && #response.status < 300}` | Expression evaluated during the response phase to determine if the response should be cached. |
| Parameters<br>`parameters` | array | | `[{"key": "retrieval_context_key", "value": "{#context.attributes['api']}_{#context.attributes['plan']}_{#context.attributes['user-id']}", "encode": true}]` | Metadata parameters attached to cached vectors for filtering and scoping. See Parameters section below. |

### Parameters (Array)

Each parameter entry defines metadata attached to cached vectors. This metadata is used to filter vector store queries and scope cache entries.

| Name<br>`json name` | Type<br>`constraint` | Mandatory | Default | Description |
|:--------------------|:---------------------|:---------:|:--------|:------------|
| Parameter name<br>`key` | string | | | The metadata key used for filtering vector store queries. |
| Parameter value<br>`value` | string | | | The metadata value, evaluated using EL. Common values include `{#context.attributes['api']}`, `{#context.attributes['plan']}`, or `{#context.attributes['user-id']}`. |
| Encode value<br>`encode` | boolean | | `false` | When `true`, hashes the parameter value using MurmurHash3 (Base64 encoded) to protect sensitive information. |